reviews.text: Im here almost every day and the worst thing is if its Rain you cant sit, why because someone put places to sit under a holes in roof. The rest is ok
No trains at the weekend currently and delays every other day.
Been stuck on the inside of a wheel for 8 months eating nothing but dirt and passengers whose dead body where on the tracks i think im in Edinburgh
Its ok... announcements are very bad quality though.

This train station is brilliant but if someone needs a train who is in a wheelchair it is hard for them to access the platform as the is no lift or ramp to use. There are only stairs. 

Also, the platform is spacious and can allow more commuters to use the trains provided. There are the relevant ticket machines and a clarke who can assist you in your commute.
